==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guillemot
<hw>Guil"le*mot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several northern sea birds, allied to the
auks. They have short legs, placed far back, and are expert divers and
swimmers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The common guillemots, or murres, belong to the genus
<gen>Uria</gen> (as <spn>U. troile</spn>); the black or foolish
guillemot (<spn>Cepphus grylle</spn>, formerly <spn>Uria grylle</spn>),
is called also <altname>sea pigeon</altname> and
<altname>eligny</altname>. See <er>Murre</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guillevat</ent>⟦br⟧
